commit.message:
Correct minimum Python version in setup.cfg

The release notes specify that the minimum supported Python version is
3.7, which is not reflected in setup.cfg.

Add marks to tests that require network access

Some Python test environments are restricted such that they can not
access any other network, which leads to some errors and failures
when testcases can not resolve names. Use pytest's marking feature to
mark them as such, so they can be more easily skipped.
